Mcaster1DNAS 2.5.0 - README
=====================================================================

Mcaster1DNAS is a streaming media server which currently supports Ogg
Vorbis, Opus, MP3, AAC, FLAC, and other audio formats. It can be used
to create an Internet radio station or a privately running jukebox and
many things in between. It is very versatile in that new formats can be
added relatively easily and supports open standards for communication
and interaction.

Based on Icecast-KH by Karl Heyes, Mcaster1DNAS extends the original
Icecast2 with advanced features, modern UI, and enhanced functionality.

Mcaster1DNAS is distributed under the GNU GPL, version 2. A copy of
this license is included with this software in the COPYING file.

NEW IN VERSION 2.5.0
=====================================================================

✨ YAML Configuration Support
  - Modern, human-readable alternative to XML
  - Automatic format detection (XML vs YAML)
  - Complete feature parity with XML
  - Four comprehensive templates provided
  - See YAML_IMPLEMENTATION.md for details

✨ YP Connection Logging
  - Per-YP-server logging for debugging directory issues
  - Optional yp-logfile parameter in configurations
  - Detailed transaction logs with timestamps
  - See YP_LOGGING_FEATURE.md for details

✨ Tabbed Admin Logs Interface
  - Modern tabbed design for log viewing
  - Access, Error, Playlist, and YP Connection logs
  - Clean UI with helpful descriptions
  - Session persistence

Prerequisites
=====================================================================
Mcaster1DNAS requires the following packages:

Required:
* libxml2 >= 2.7 - http://xmlsoft.org/downloads.html
* libxslt >= 1.1 - http://xmlsoft.org/XSLT/downloads.html
* curl >= 7.10 - http://curl.haxx.se/download.html
  NOTE: Mcaster1DNAS may be compiled without curl, however this will
        disable all Directory server interaction (YP).
* ogg/vorbis >= 1.0 - http://www.vorbis.com/files

Optional:
* libyaml >= 0.1.7 - YAML configuration support
  Debian/Ubuntu: apt-get install libyaml-dev
  RHEL/CentOS:   yum install libyaml-devel

* OpenSSL >= 1.0 - HTTPS/SSL support
  Most Linux distributions include OpenSSL by default

A Note About Package Management
=====================================================================
If your operating system uses package managers (apt, yum, dnf, etc.):

You will need to install the "development" or "devel" packages for
each prerequisite in addition to the normal packages.

Example on Debian/Ubuntu:
  sudo apt-get install libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev \
                       libvorbis-dev libyaml-dev libssl-dev

Example on RHEL/CentOS:
  sudo yum install libxml2-devel libxslt-devel curl-devel \
                   libvorbis-devel libyaml-devel openssl-devel

Build/Install
=====================================================================
To build Mcaster1DNAS on a Unix platform:

Standard Build:
   ./autogen.sh
   ./configure
   make
   make install

Build with YAML and SSL support (recommended):
   ./autogen.sh
   ./configure --with-yaml --with-openssl
   make
   make install

Build with custom prefix:
   ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/mcaster1dnas \
               --with-yaml --with-openssl
   make
   make install

Configure Options:
  --with-yaml       Enable YAML configuration support (requires libyaml)
  --with-openssl    Enable SSL/HTTPS support (requires OpenSSL)
  --prefix=PATH     Installation directory (default: /usr/local)

Configuration
=====================================================================

Sample configuration files are installed in:
  - /usr/local/etc/mcaster1.xml (XML format - traditional)
  - /usr/local/share/mcaster1/ (YAML templates)

YAML Templates Provided:
  - mcaster1.yaml.in               - Comprehensive template (recommended)
  - mcaster1_minimal.yaml.in       - Minimal configuration
  - mcaster1_shoutcast_compat.yaml.in - Shoutcast DSP compatibility
  - mcaster1_advanced.yaml.in      - All advanced features

Starting the Server:

With XML config:
   mcaster1 -c /etc/mcaster1.xml

With YAML config:
   mcaster1 -c /etc/mcaster1.yaml

The server automatically detects whether your config is XML or YAML!

YP Directory Logging (NEW):

To enable YP connection logging for debugging directory listing issues:

YAML format:
   directories:
     - yp-url: "http://dir.example.com/yp"
       yp-logfile: "/var/log/mcaster1/yp.log"

XML format:
   <directory>
       <yp-url>http://dir.example.com/yp</yp-url>
       <yp-logfile>/var/log/mcaster1/yp.log</yp-logfile>
   </directory>

Admin Interface
=====================================================================
Access the web admin interface at:
   http://your-server:port/admin/

Default credentials (CHANGE THESE!):
   Username: admin
   Password: hackme

Features:
   - Real-time statistics dashboard
   - Mount point management
   - Listener management
   - Relay configuration
   - Tabbed log viewer (Access, Error, Playlist, YP)
   - Modern UI with live updates

