Support
=====================================================================
For help, questions, or to report issues:

   Email:   mcaster1@xiph.org
   IRC:     irc.freenode.net #mcaster1
   GitHub:  https://github.com/mcaster1/mcaster1dnas (if available)

When reporting issues, please include:
   - Mcaster1DNAS version (mcaster1 -v)
   - Operating system and version
   - Configuration file (sanitized - remove passwords!)
   - Relevant log entries from error.log

Quick Start Guide
=====================================================================

1. Install Prerequisites:
   apt-get install libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev \
                   libvorbis-dev libyaml-dev libssl-dev

2. Build and Install:
   ./autogen.sh
   ./configure --with-yaml --with-openssl
   make
   sudo make install

3. Copy Configuration Template:
   cp conf/mcaster1.yaml.in /etc/mcaster1.yaml

4. Edit Configuration:
   vi /etc/mcaster1.yaml
   # Set hostname, passwords, ports, etc.

5. Create Log Directory:
   mkdir -p /var/log/mcaster1
   chown mcaster1:mcaster1 /var/log/mcaster1

6. Start Server:
   mcaster1 -c /etc/mcaster1.yaml

7. Test in Browser:
   http://your-server:8000/status.xsl

8. Access Admin:
   http://your-server:8000/admin/

Security Notes
=====================================================================

IMPORTANT SECURITY STEPS:

1. Change ALL default passwords in your configuration:
   - admin-password
   - source-password
   - relay-password

2. Use HTTPS for admin interface (configure SSL certificate)

3. Restrict admin access by IP if possible

4. Keep your server and dependencies updated

5. Review and customize authentication settings

6. Consider running server as non-root user (recommended)

7. Enable firewall rules to limit access

Performance Tips
=====================================================================

For high-traffic servers:

1. Increase system limits:
   - File descriptors (ulimit -n)
   - TCP buffer sizes

2. Configure appropriate worker count:
   workers: 2-4 (based on CPU cores)

3. Adjust queue and burst sizes:
   queue-size: 524288
   burst-size: 65536

4. Enable bandwidth limiting per mount if needed

5. Monitor logs for performance issues

6. Consider using a CDN for high listener counts

